  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Validation results were generated using the production solver configuration ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7-rc2, which the assessment team characterises as effectively the same build as the released version ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7. No re-execution of validation runs was performed under the released build; the team relied on the assertion that the rc2-to-release delta introduced only documentation and installer changes. Decision: Accepted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
